t\":\"**Considering actor construction**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to construct actors without directly using reflection. In using the public API, it seems like classOf is okay. But for native construction, if I'm using actors, I might need metadata. To avoid that, I can use `Props(new NoopActor)`, which seems to skip reflection. However, using Props.apply with a creator function might still capture and invoke some level of reflection. It's a bit tricky!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_RGlawmiXBHwf5Rvz7RxaD6KP|fc_0d4d08b486d569410169fd690e249c81a1bd5fb7b2a5576e14", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-serialization-jackson_3/1.0.1/src/test/scala/org_apache_pekko/pekko_serialization_jackson_3/Pekko_serialization_jackson_3Test.scala", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.apache.pekko.actor.ActorSystem\nimport org.apache.pekko.actor.Address\n", "newText": "import org.apache.pekko.actor.Actor\nimport org.apache.pekko.actor.ActorRef\nimport org.apache.pekko.actor.ActorSystem\nimport org.apache.pekko.actor.Address\nimport org.apache.pekko.actor.Props\n"}, {"oldText": "final case class NumberBox(count: Int)\n\nfinal case class VersionedProfile(id: String, displayName: String, active: Boolean)\n", "newText": "final case class NumberBox(count: Int)\n\nfinal case class ActorRoute(id: String, recipient: ActorRef, replyTo: ActorRef)\n\nfinal case class VersionedProfile(id: String, displayName: String, active: Boolean)\n\nclass NoopActor extends Actor {\n  override def receive: Receive = { case _ => () }\n}\n"}, {"oldText": "  @Test\n  def jsonSerializerMigratesOlderPayloadsBeforeDeserialization(): Unit = withActorSystem(\n", "newText": "  @Test\n  def jsonSerializerRoundTripsClassicActorReferences(): Unit = withActorSystem(\n    \"actor-ref\",\n    BaseConfig + \"\"\"\n      pekko.actor.serialization-bindings {\n        \"org_apache_pekko.pekko_serialization_jackson_3.ActorRoute\" = jackson-json\n      }\n      \"\"\"\n  ) { system =>\n    val recipient: ActorRef = system.actorOf(Props(new NoopActor), \"recipient\")\n    val route: ActorRoute = ActorRoute(\"route-1\", recipient, system.deadLetters)\n    val serializer: SerializerWithStringManifest = jacksonSerializerFor(system, route)\n    val restored: ActorRoute = serializer.fromBinary(serializer.toBinary(route), serializer.manifest(route)).asInstanceOf[ActorRoute]\n\n    assertThat(restored.id).isEqualTo(route.id)\n    assertThat(restored.recipient).isEqualTo(recipient)\n    assertThat(restored.replyTo).isEqualTo(system.deadLetters)\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def jsonSerializerMigratesOlderPayloadsBeforeDeserialization(): Unit = withActorSystem(\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2658, "output": 1742, "cacheRead": 19456, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23856, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778215166181, "responseId": "resp_0d4d08b486d569410169fd68fef1a481a1b75fec1874a7529f"}}
